The Ministry of Labor, War Invalids, and Social Affairs will conduct a survey on the impact of toxic chemicals from the Vietnam War.
Victims will receive support managed by the Red Cross, funded by donations primarily from domestic victims of Agent Orange.
Recent studies show a decrease in dioxin levels, but the toxic defoliant continues to affect multiple generations.
Despite ongoing demining efforts, buried dioxin remains a concern.
The US and Vietnam recently dedicated a site, highlighting the lasting effects of Agent Orange.
Efforts to support victims and address health issues persist, with calls for increased international assistance.
